text: James Kaylor "Jim" Leedy (October 3, 1925 – September 5, 1983) was a former member of the Ohio Senate, serving from the 19th District from 1967-. His district encompassed much of North-Central Ohio. ==References== Category:1924 births Category:Ohio state senators Category:Ohio Republicans Category:1983 deaths Category:20th-century American politicians Category:People from Shreve, Ohio
